quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  21,11,"˹Imagine˺ how many societies of wrongdoers We have destroyed, raising up other people after them"
  21,12,"When the wrongdoers sensed ˹the arrival of˺ Our torment, they started to run away from their cities"
  21,13,"˹They were told,˺ “Do not run away! Return to your luxuries and your homes, so you may be questioned ˹about your fate˺.”"
  21,14,"They cried, “Woe to us! We have surely been wrongdoers.”"
  21,15,"They kept repeating their cry until We mowed them down, ˹leaving them˺ lifeless"
  21,16,We did not create the heavens and the earth and everything in between for sport
  21,17,"Had We intended to take ˹some˺ amusement, We could have found it in Our presence, if that had been Our Will"
  21,18,"In fact, We hurl the truth against falsehood, leaving it crushed, and it quickly vanishes. And woe be to you for what you claim"
  21,19,"To Him belong all those in the heavens and the earth. And those nearest to Him are not too proud to worship Him, nor do they tire"
  21,20,"They glorify ˹Him˺ day and night, never wavering"
  21,21,"Or have they taken gods from the earth, who can raise the dead"
  21,22,"Had there been other gods besides God in the heavens or the earth, both ˹realms˺ would have surely been corrupted. So Glorified is God, Lord of the Throne, far above what they claim"
  21,23,"He cannot be questioned about what He does, but they will ˹all˺ be questioned"
  21,24,"Or have they taken other gods besides Him? Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “Show ˹me˺ your proof. Here is ˹the Quran,˺ the Reminder for those with me; along with ˹earlier Scriptures,˺ the Reminder for those before me.” But most of them do not know the truth, so they turn away"